# 🟢 Express.js Backend Explained

---

## 📌 Overview

This backend is built using Node.js and Express.js.

---

## ⚙️ Core Components

### Express Server
Handles HTTP requests and routes.

### Middleware
- express.json() → Parses JSON requests  
- cors() → Enables cross-origin requests  

---

## 🗄️ Database

Uses SQLite with better-sqlite3.

---

## 🔗 Routes

### GET /api/students
Fetch all students

### POST /api/students
Add a new student

### PUT /api/students/:id
Update full record

### PATCH /api/students/:id
Update partial data

### DELETE /api/students/:id
Delete student

---

## 🧠 Key Concepts

- req.body → Data from frontend  
- req.params → URL parameters  
- .all() → Multiple rows  
- .get() → Single row  

---

## 🎯 Summary

This backend connects frontend requests with database operations using REST APIs.
